iner is a pure function component — layout mode computed from terminalWidth prop on every render. No cached state.\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | grep \"re-evaluates layout\"\n```\n```output\n ✓ lib/__tests__/ink-lane-container.test.tsx > LaneContainer component > re-evaluates layout when terminalWidth changes 18ms\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Result |\n|----|--------|\n| 1 | PASS |\n| 2 | PASS |\n| 3 | PASS |\n| 4 | PASS |\n| 5 | PASS |\n| 6 | PASS |\n| 7 | PASS |\n| 8 | PASS |\n| 9 | PASS |\n| 10 | PASS |\n| 11 | PASS |\n| 12 | PASS |\n\n**Final Result: ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs)**\n","numLines":182,"startLine":1,"totalLines":182}}}
