{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CqPxdGFkuE1CcXATabrp3Y","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e3ded59-6184-4f8b-8f55-ba5e63dae51f","uuid":"27315b02-2f3c-4597-a3e5-21bf2f59d5ae","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:45:19.723Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Redundant operations: One Edit reverted (Separator import causing circular dep)","newString":"- Redundant operations: One Edit reverted (Separator import causing circular dep)\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (session 7)\n\n### 20-1-lane-container-lane-components — verification (2026-04-04T02:42)\n\n- Tier A quick-win — proof already existed with ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Only needed `codeharness verify` validation.\n- No issues encountered.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 1 (subagent)\n- By tool: Bash: 1\n- Files read: 1 (proof document in parent)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 20-2-summary-bar-merge-status — create-story (2026-04-04T02:45)\n\n- No problems encountered. Epic definition clear.\n- Risk: AC #12 (single-lane hides SummaryBar/MergeStatus) — dev must not regress existing single-lane conditional logic in ink-app.tsx.\n- Observation: UX spec shows Ctrl+M toggling merge detail — scoped to 20-3, not this story.\n- Observation: Architecture doc lists ink-summary-bar.tsx and ink-merge-status.tsx as separate files.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 11\n- By tool: Read: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 3, Write: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04\n\n### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — verification (2026-04-04T01:10)\n\n- Proof document used `### AC N:` headers instead of `## AC N:` — validator couldn't parse. Fixed by rewriting proof.\n- No `bash`+`output` code block pairs in original proof — added evidence blocks.\n- Subagent misreported test compilation failure (Babel/Jest) when project uses vitest.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 5\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — create-story (2026-04-04T01:13)\n\n- No project-context.md found — context gathered from architecture and epics files.\n- Workaround: inline AsyncMutex class pattern rather than npm dependency.\n- Risk: AC #7 (NFR4 timing) depends on repo size/disk speed, tagged runtime-provable.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Read: 10, Grep: 3, Glob: 4, Bash: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — dev-story (2026-04-04T01:17)\n\n- Branch coverage gap (91.17%): defensive catch blocks hard to trigger in isolation.\n- Test output parsing simplistic — regex for vitest/jest only, falls back for other runners.\n- promisify mock coupling: tests depend on module's use of `promisify(exec)`.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 7, Bash: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest coverage (~30 lines), vitest test (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — code-review (2026-04-04T01:22)\n\n- HIGH: Shell injection via testCommand parameter — fixed with regex validation.\n- HIGH: Shell injection via malicious branch names — fixed with regex validation.\n- MEDIUM: TOCTOU race on branch existence — fixed with re-verification inside mutex.\n- MEDIUM: Missing `// IGNORE:` comment on catch block — fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): No mutex acquisition timeout — starvation risk.\n- LOW (unfixed): No logging in merge path.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput only reads stdout, not stderr.\n- Architecture: testCommand as raw shell string; safer would be execFile with array args.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:coverage (~60 lines x2)\n- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n- Redundant operations: test:coverage ran twice (once pre-fix, once post-fix)\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — verification (2026-04-04T01:27)\n\n- BATS test failures (253 `not ok`): pre-existing, not related to story 18-1.\n- AC 7 (runtime-provable) timing NFR4 can't be fully verified with mocked git ops — durationMs mechanism confirmed but 30-second bound untested.\n- npm test ran 4 times in verification subagent (wasteful).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Grep: 1, Write: 1, other: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~40 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: npm test ran 4 times to extract different parts\n\n### 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution — create-story (2026-04-04T01:40)\n\n- No project-context.md found — context gathered from architecture and previous story.\n- onConflict callback design chosen to keep worktree-manager decoupled from merge agent.\n- Risk: Agent may not commit after resolving conflicts — detection logic left to implementation.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff --stat (~8 lines), git log --oneline (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads (worktree-manager.ts read 3x at different offsets)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution — dev-story (2026-04-04T01:50)\n\n- onConflict callback passes `driver: undefined as never` — WorktreeManager doesn't hold a driver reference. Caller must