: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git log --oneline -5 (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One extra Glob for config path\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — dev-story (2026-04-04T02:18)\n\n- writeMergeTelemetry had to be exported for merge-agent two-phase pattern (validate then write telemetry on success). Story spec didn't explicitly require this but it's needed.\n- Branch coverage 96.42% — uncovered branch is nullish coalescing fallback on err.stdout (Istanbul instrumentation edge case).\n- worktree-manager.test.ts read 4 times due to token limits.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 26\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 13, Write: 2, Glob: 4\n- Largest Bash outputs: tsc --noEmit (~32 lines), vitest --coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 12 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n- Redundant operations: worktree-manager.test.ts chunked reads, one broken edit fix\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — code-review (2026-04-04T02:27)\n\n- HIGH: coverage type mismatch (undefined vs null) across validator, worktree-manager, merge-agent. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing maxBuffer on exec could truncate large test output. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing stderr capture loses diagnostic info. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Telemetry object not typed against canonical TelemetryEntry. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput first-match regex could pick per-suite counts.\n- LOW (unfixed): writeMergeTelemetry duplicates NDJSON write logic from telemetry-writer.ts.\n- No integration test for full merge-then-validate flow with real git repo.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 16, Grep: 6, Glob: 5, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest run verbose (~50 lines), git diff (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One redundant glob search for workflow file\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — verification (2026-04-04T02:40)\n\n- `codeharness verify` precondition failure: AGENTS.md was stale for `src/lib` — missing `cross-worktree-validator.ts`. Fixed in parent orchestrator.\n- Coverage for `cross-worktree-validator.ts` specifically could not be isolated to an exact percentage from coverage tool output. Story completion notes claim 100% and all 33 tests exercise every code path.\n- Prior session completed create/dev/review but crashed before updating sprint-status.yaml from `backlog`. Orchestrator detected the mismatch and advanced status.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:unit (~80 lines), vitest --reporter=verbose (~80 lines), npm run test:coverage (~50 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two separate coverage commands that didn't yield isolated file percentage\n\n### 19-1-epic-completion-detection — create-story (2026-04-04T02:54)\n\n- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent (per instructions) — orchestrator handled.\n- No config.yaml at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — found at `_bmad/config.yaml` instead.\n- No project-context.md found — not a blocker, sufficient context from epics/architecture.\n- EpicState.status is `string` not a union type — story handles via local `EpicLifecycleStatus` type.\n- All 10 ACs tagged test-provable — pure functions, no I/O.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 10, Glob: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff HEAD~3 --name-only (~35 lines), sprint-state.json (~40 lines), git log (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 19-1-epic-completion-detection — dev-story (2026-04-04T02:57)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 13\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 3, Edit: 4, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~30 lines), vitest run (~10 lines), npm run build (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total