{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BpZgVb6sCmtHhHtTr4S7iJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 20.2: Summary Bar & Merge Status\n2\t\n3\tStatus: backlog\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to see done/merging/pending counts and merge progress in the TUI,\n11\tso that I know the sprint's overall state at a glance.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new `src/lib/ink-summary-bar.tsx`, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `SummaryBar` React component that accepts `SummaryBarProps` (doneStories: string[], mergingEpic: MergingEpicInfo | null, pendingEpics: string[]) and renders a one-line summary in the format: `Done: {stories} │ Merging: {epic} → main ◌ │ Pending: {epics}`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t2. **Given** no epic is currently merging (`mergingEpic` is null), **when** `SummaryBar` renders, **then** the Merging section displays `Merging: —`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t3. **Given** a `mergingEpic` with status `'in-progress'`, **when** `SummaryBar` renders, **then** the Merging section displays the epic name with a spinner indicator: `Merging: epic-{N} → main ◌`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t4. **Given** a `mergingEpic` with status `'resolving'` and a `conflictCount`, **when** `SummaryBar` renders, **then** the Merging section displays: `Merging: epic-{N} → main (resolving {X} conflict(s)) ◌` in yellow. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t5. **Given** a new `src/lib/ink-merge-status.tsx`, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `MergeStatus` React component that accepts `MergeStatusProps` (mergeState: MergeState | null) and renders detailed merge progress below the summary bar. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t6. **Given** a `mergeState` with outcome `'clean'`, **when** `MergeStatus` renders, **then** it displays a green line: `[OK] Merge epic-{N} → main: clean (0 conflicts)`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t7. **Given** a `mergeState` with outcome `'resolved'` and resolved conflict details, **when** `MergeStatus` renders, **then** it displays: `[OK] Merge epic-{N} → main: {X} conflict(s) auto-resolved` followed by indented file paths. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t8. **Given** a `mergeState` with outcome `'escalated'`, **when** `MergeStatus` renders, **then** it displays a red `[FAIL]` line with the reason and preserved worktree path. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t9. **Given** a `mergeState` with `testResults` (passed count, coverage), **when** `MergeStatus` renders, **then** it displays post-merge test results: `[OK] Tests: {passed}/{total} passed ({duration}s)` in green, or `[FAIL] Tests: ...` in red if any failed. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t10. **Given** a lane completes all its stories, **when** `SummaryBar` renders, **then** a lane completion line is displayed: `[OK] Lane {N}: Epic {X} complete ({stories} stories, ${cost}, {time})`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t11. **Given** the `ink-app.tsx` root component, **when** updated to integrate `SummaryBar` and `MergeStatus`, **then** they render between the lane section and the activity section (after `LaneContainer` / single-lane layout, before `CompletedTools`), separated by `<Separator />` lines. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t12. **Given** `max_parallel: 1` (single lane mode), **when** the TUI renders, **then** neither `SummaryBar` nor `MergeStatus` render — they are only visible during multi-lane execution. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n38\t\n39\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n40\t\n41\t- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/ink-summary-bar.tsx` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #10)\n42\t  - [ ] Define `MergingEpicInfo` interface: `{ epicId: string; status: 'in-progress' | 'resolving' | 'complete'; conflictCount?: number }`\n43\t  - [ ] Define `SummaryBarProps` interface with doneStories, mergingEpic, pendingEpics, completedLanes\n44\t  - [ ] Define `CompletedLaneInfo` interface: `{ laneIndex: number; epicId: string; storyCount: number; cost: number; elapsed: string }`\n45\t  - [ ] Implement `SummaryBar` component: done section (green ✓ per story), merging section (yellow when resolving, dim when idle), pending section (dim list)\n46\t  - [ ] Implement lane completion line rendering: `[OK] Lane N: Epic X complete (...)` in green\n47\t  - [ ] Format done stories as `{key} ✓` with green color\n48\t  - [ ] Handle empty states: no done stories → `Done: —`, no pending → `Pending: —`\n49\t\n50\t- [ ] Task 2: Create `src/lib/ink-merge-status.tsx` (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8, #9)\n51\t  - [ ] Define `MergeState` interface: `{ epicId: string; outcome: 'clean' | 'resolved' | 'escalated' | 'in-progress'; conflicts?: string[]; conflictCount?: number; testResults?: { passed: number; failed: number; total: number; durationSecs: number; coverage: number | null }; worktreePath?: string; reason?: string }`\n52\t  - [ ] Implement `MergeStatus` component: dispatch on outcome for rendering\n53\t  - [ ] Clean merge: green `[OK]` line\n54\t  - [ ] Resolved merge: green `[OK]` line + indented resolved file paths\n55\t  - [ ] Escalated merge: red `[FAIL]` line with reason + preserved worktree path\n56\t  - [ ] Test results: green `[OK]` or red `[FAIL]` depending on failure count\n57\t  - [ ] Render nothing when `mergeState` is null (no active/recent merge)\n58\t\n59\t- [ ] Task 3: Integrate into `ink-app.tsx` (AC: #11, #12)\n60\t  - [ ] Import `SummaryBar` from `./ink-summary-bar.js` and `MergeStatus` from `./ink-merge-status.js`\n61\t  - [ ] Add conditional rendering: only show when `laneCount > 1`\n62\t  - [ ] Place between lane section and activity section with `<Separator />` delimiters\n63\t  - [ ] Add `summaryBar` and `mergeState` fields to `RendererState` interface in `ink-components.tsx`\n64\t\n65\t- [ ] Task 4: Extend `RendererState` in `ink-components.tsx` (AC: #11)\n66\t  - [ ] Add optional `summaryBar` field with type from `ink-summary-bar.tsx`\n67\t  - [ ] Add optional `mergeState` field with type from `ink-merge-status.tsx`\n68\t\n69\t- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests for `src/lib/__tests__/ink-summary-bar.test.tsx` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #10)\n70\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar renders done stories with ✓ symbols\n71\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar renders `Merging: —` when no merge active\n72\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar renders merging epic with spinner when in-progress\n73\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar renders resolving merge in yellow with conflict count\n74\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar renders pending epics list\n75\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar renders lane completion line\n76\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar handles empty done/pending lists with `—` fallback\n77\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar exports correct types\n78\t\n79\t- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests for `src/lib/__tests__/ink-merge-status.test.tsx` (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8, #9)\n80\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus renders nothing when mergeState is null\n81\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus renders clean merge in green\n82\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus renders resolved merge with file paths\n83\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus renders escalated merge in red with worktree path\n84\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus renders passing test results in green\n85\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus renders failing test results in red\n86\t  - [ ] Test: MergeStatus exports correct types\n87\t\n88\t- [ ] Task 7: Write integration tests for `ink-app.tsx` changes (AC: #11, #12)\n89\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar and MergeStatus render when laneCount > 1\n90\t  - [ ] Test: SummaryBar and MergeStatus do NOT render when laneCount <= 1\n91\t\n92\t## Dev Notes\n93\t\n94\t### Architecture Constraints\n95\t\n96\t- **Architecture Decision 8** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The Ink render tree hierarchy places `SummaryBar` and `MergeStatus` between the lane section and the activity section. They are first-class display elements, not sub-components of Lane or LaneContainer.\n97\t- **TUI Boundary**: SummaryBar and MergeStatus are purely presentational. They receive data via props — no direct access to lane pool, worktree manager, or merge agent. Event routing (20-3) will wire real data into these props.\n98\t- **Single Ink instance**: All components feed into the same Ink render loop.\n99\t- **NFR2**: Multi-lane TUI must render at 15 FPS with up to 4 concurrent lanes.\n100\t\n101\t### What This Story Actually Does\n102\t\n103\tThis story creates two new Ink components for the **sprint-level status layer**:\n104\t\n105\t1. `SummaryBar` — one-line overview: done stories, merge status, pending epics\n106\t2. `MergeStatus` — detailed merge progress: clean/resolved/escalated outcomes, test results\n107\t\n108\tIt also:\n109\t3. Extends `RendererState` to carry summary and merge data\n110\t4. Integrates both components into `ink-app.tsx` (conditional on multi-lane mode)\n111\t5. Ensures single-lane mode is unaffected\n112\t\n113\tThis is a pure presentational story. No event routing, no merge execution, no lane management.\n114\t\n115\t### Key Files to Create\n116\t\n117\t| File | Why |\n118\t|------|-----|\n119\t| `src/lib/ink-summary-bar.tsx` | New — summary bar component (done/merging/pending) |\n120\t| `src/lib/ink-merge-status.tsx` | New — merge status detail component |\n121\t| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-summary-bar.test.tsx` | Tests for SummaryBar |\n122\t| `src/lib/__tests__/ink-merge-status.test.tsx` | Tests for MergeStatus |\n123\t\n124\t### Key Files to Modify\n125\t\n126\t| File | Why |\n127\t|------|-----|\n128\t| `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` | Integrate SummaryBar and MergeStatus into render tree |\n129\t| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | Extend RendererState with summary/merge data |\n130\t\n131\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n132\t\n133\t| File | Why |\n134\t|------|-----|\n135\t| `src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx` | `LaneContainer`, `LaneData` — renders above SummaryBar |\n136\t| `src/lib/ink-lane.tsx` | `Lane`, `StoryProgressEntry` — per-lane display |\n137\t| `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` | Activity display — renders below MergeStatus |\n138\t| `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` | `RendererHandle`, `RendererState` — drives re-renders |\n139\t| `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` | `SprintInfo`, `RendererState`, `Separator` — existing types and components |\n140\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | `MergeResult`, `MergeConflictInfo` — merge outcome types |\n141\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LaneEvent`, `LaneStatus` — lane lifecycle events |\n142\t| `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` | `MergeConflictContext` — conflict resolution types |\n143\t\n144\t### Component Hierarchy (Target State)\n145\t\n146\t```\n147\t<App>\n148\t  <Header />                       ← Already extended (20-1) with lane count\n149\t  <LaneContainer>                  ← Already created (20-1)\n150\t    <Lane epic={10}> ... </Lane>\n151\t    <Lane epic={14}> ... </Lane>\n152\t    <CollapsedLanes />\n153\t  </LaneContainer>\n154\t  <Separator />\n155\t  <SummaryBar />                   ← NEW: done, merging, pending\n156\t  <Separator />\n157\t  <MergeStatus />                  ← NEW: merge progress, conflicts, test results\n158\t  <Separator />\n159\t  <CompletedTools />               ← Existing: activity section unchanged\n160\t  <ActiveTool />\n161\t  <LastThought />\n162\t  <RetryNotice />\n163\t</App>\n164\t```\n165\t\n166\t### Existing Patterns to Follow\n167\t\n168\t- **Component file naming**: `ink-{name}.tsx` — pure presentational components.\n169\t- **Import style**: `import React from 'react'` + `import { Text, Box } from 'ink'` — standard Ink pattern.\n170\t- **ESM imports**: Use `.js` extensions in TypeScript ESM imports (`'./ink-summary-bar.js'`).\n171\t- **Type exports**: Types at top of component file, then components.\n172\t- **No hooks**: Existing components are stateless (state from parent via props). `SummaryBar` and `MergeStatus` should be pure function components.\n173\t- **Symbols**: Done `✓`, active `◆`, pending `○`, spinner `◌` — already used throughout.\n174\t- **Color scheme**: Green for success/done, yellow for warnings/in-progress, red for failure, dim for inactive/pending.\n175\t- **Status prefixes**: `[OK]`, `[FAIL]`, `[WARN]`, `[INFO]` — established pattern from UX spec.\n176\t- **Separator**: Reuse `<Separator />` from `ink-components.tsx` between sections.\n177\t- **Ink testing**: Use `ink-testing-library` render function. See `src/lib/__tests__/ink-*.test.tsx`.\n178\t\n179\t### UX Display Formats\n180\t\n181\t**Summary bar (one line):**\n182\t```\n183\tDone: 10-1 ✓  10-2 ✓  10-3 ✓  14-1 ✓ │ Merging: — │ Pending: epic-12, epic-13\n184\t```\n185\t\n186\t**Summary bar during active merge:**\n187\t```\n188\tDone: 10-1 ✓  10-2 ✓ │ Merging: epic-14 → main ◌ │ Pending: epic-11, epic-12\n189\t```\n190\t\n191\t**Summary bar during conflict resolution:**\n192\t```\n193\tDone: ... │ Merging: epic-11 → main (resolving 1 conflict) ◌ │ Pending: ...\n194\t```\n195\t\n196\t**Merge status — clean:**\n197\t```\n198\t[OK] Merge epic-14 → main: clean (0 conflicts)\n199\t[OK] Tests: 1650/1650 passed (18s)\n200\t[OK] Worktree cleaned: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-14\n201\t```\n202\t\n203\t**Merge status — resolved:**\n204\t```\n205\t[OK] Merge epic-11 → main: 1 conflict auto-resolved\n206\t     └ src/lib/workflow-engine.ts: additive changes in different functions\n207\t[OK] Tests: 1652/1652 passed (19s)\n208\t```\n209\t\n210\t**Merge status — escalated:**\n211\t```\n212\t[FAIL] Merge epic-11 → main: conflict unresolvable after 3 attempts\n213\t       └ src/lib/workflow-engine.ts: semantic conflict in dispatchTaskWithResult()\n214\t       → Manual resolution required\n215\t       → Worktree preserved: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-11\n216\t```\n217\t\n218\t**Lane completion:**\n219\t```\n220\t[OK] Lane 2: Epic 14 complete (3 stories, $4.80, 22m)\n221\t```\n222\t\n223\t### Previous Story (20-1) Intelligence\n224\t\n225\t- Story 20-1 created `ink-lane.tsx` (~80-120 lines) and `ink-lane-container.tsx` (~120-180 lines).\n226\t- Extended `Header` with `laneCount` and `laneTotalCost`.\n227\t- Added `lanes?: LaneData[]` to `RendererState`.\n228\t- Testing pattern: vitest, `vi.mock`, `ink-testing-library`, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`.\n229\t- ESM module pattern: `.js` extensions in imports.\n230\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`.\n231\t- 187 test files, 5062 tests pass — zero regressions after 20-1.\n232\t\n233\t### Edge Cases\n234\t\n235\t- **No done stories**: Display `Done: —` (em dash, not empty).\n236\t- **No pending epics**: Display `Pending: —`.\n237\t- **No active merge**: Display `Merging: —`.\n238\t- **Multiple merges queued**: Only one merge can run at a time (merge serialization from 18-1). Show the active one.\n239\t- **Merge with 0 conflicts but test failure**: Show `[OK] Merge ... clean` then `[FAIL] Tests: ...`.\n240\t- **MergeStatus with null state**: Render nothing (component returns null).\n241\t- **Very long list of done stories**: May need truncation or wrapping for narrow terminals.\n242\t- **Cost = 0**: Display `$0.00`.\n243\t- **Coverage = null**: Omit coverage from test results display.\n244\t\n245\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n246\t\n247\t- **Lane event routing** — That's story 20-3.\n248\t- **Wiring real merge data into MergeStatus** — That's 20-3 (event routing connects live merge events to renderer state).\n249\t- **Activity display lane filtering** — That's story 20-3.\n250\t- **Ctrl+L / Ctrl+M keybindings** — That's story 20-3.\n251\t- **Merge execution logic** — Already exists in `worktree-manager.ts` (18-1) and `merge-agent.ts` (18-2).\n252\t- **Lane pool management** — Already exists in `lane-pool.ts` (17-2).\n253\t\n254\t### Project Structure Notes\n255\t\n256\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n257\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n258\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n259\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`\n260\t- New `.tsx` files for React/Ink components\n261\t- Keep each new component file focused: `ink-summary-bar.tsx` (~80-120 lines), `ink-merge-status.tsx` (~100-150 lines)\n262\t\n263\t### References\n264\t\n265\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 20.2]\n266\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 8 -- Multi-Lane TUI Architecture]\n267\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Merge Status Display]\n268\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Summary Bar]\n269\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Component Architecture]\n270\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-app.tsx]\n271\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx#RendererState]\n272\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-lane-container.tsx#LaneData]\n273\t- [Source: src/lib/worktree-manager.ts#MergeResult]\n274\t- [Source: src/lib/lane-pool.ts#LaneEvent]\n275\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lyf5tpvBU7eZNwMupgDFgG","session_id":"7e3ded59-6184-4f8b-8f55-ba5e63dae51f","uuid":"e7592a18-42aa-41b5-9674-cce8725b7d4c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:45:43.308Z"}
