{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TzQwpEV7uekTzzh7pB5DWd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Code Review Findings\n\n**Story:** 20-2-summary-bar-merge-status.md\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 2 Medium, 2 Low\n\n### HIGH Issues (fixed)\n\n1. **Missing separator between MergeStatus and activity section in multi-lane mode** — When `state.stories.length === 0` (which is expected in multi-lane mode where stories are per-lane), no `<Separator />` rendered between MergeStatus/SummaryBar and the CompletedTools activity section. AC #11 requires separator delimiters. Fixed in `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` (line 51) — separator now also renders when `laneCount > 1 && (state.summaryBar || state.mergeState)`.\n\n### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n\n2. **Missing test for resolving merge without conflictCount** — `SummaryBar` handles `resolving` status when `conflictCount` is undefined (renders without parenthetical), but no test covered this edge case. Added test in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-summary-bar.test.tsx`.\n\n3. **Missing test for separator in multi-lane mode without stories** — The separator fix needed test coverage. Added test in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-app.test.tsx`.\n\n### LOW Issues (not fixed)\n\n4. **Tests don't verify color rendering** — AC #4 specifies yellow for resolving, AC #6/7 specify green for clean/resolved, AC #8 specifies red for escalated. Tests check content only, not ANSI color codes. Ink testing library makes color assertions possible but awkward. The color IS implemented in the components correctly.\n\n5. **`in-progress` outcome in MergeStatus lacks status prefix** — All other outcomes use `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` prefix pattern; `in-progress` renders as plain `Merging epic-N → main ◌`. This is by design (it's transitional state) but inconsistent with the prefix convention.\n\n### Results After Fixes\n\n- Tests: 190 files, 5103 tests, 0 failures\n- Coverage: 96.79% overall (target: 90%)\n- Per-file floor: all 186 files above 80%\n- Story status updated to `verifying`\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/ink-app.tsx` — separator fix\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-summary-bar.test.tsx` — edge case test added\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-app.test.tsx` — separator test added\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/20-2-summary-bar-merge-status.md` — status to verifying\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Missing `<Separator />` between MergeStatus and activity section in multi-lane mode when `stories` array is empty\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** No test for `resolving` merge status when `conflictCount` is undefined\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** No test for separator rendering in multi-lane mode without stories\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Tests do not verify ANSI color output for any component — yellow/green/red assertions rely on content only\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `in-progress` outcome in MergeStatus lacks `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` prefix, inconsistent with other outcomes\n- Coverage gaps: none — all story files at 100% statement coverage\n- Architecture concerns: none — components follow existing patterns, pure presentational, no coupling to business logic\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx tsc --noEmit` (~42 lines), `npx vitest run` full suite (~10 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage | grep ink` (~4 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: one re-read of ink-app.tsx was cached/skipped by the tool; two separate `vitest --coverage | grep ink` calls could have been combined"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac3bf7137bcfa9dae (use SendMessage with to: 'ac3bf7137bcfa9dae' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60260\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 26826