ken Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git log --oneline -5 (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One extra Glob for config path\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — dev-story (2026-04-04T02:18)\n\n- writeMergeTelemetry had to be exported for merge-agent two-phase pattern (validate then write telemetry on success). Story spec didn't explicitly require this but it's needed.\n- Branch coverage 96.42% — uncovered branch is nullish coalescing fallback on err.stdout (Istanbul instrumentation edge case).\n- worktree-manager.test.ts read 4 times due to token limits.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 26\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 13, Write: 2, Glob: 4\n- Largest Bash outputs: tsc --noEmit (~32 lines), vitest --coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 12 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n- Redundant operations: worktree-manager.test.ts chunked reads, one broken edit fix\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — code-review (2026-04-04T02:27)\n\n- HIGH: coverage type mismatch (undefined vs null) across validator, worktree-manager, merge-agent. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing maxBuffer on exec could truncate large test output. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing stderr capture loses diagnostic info. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Telemetry object not typed against canonical TelemetryEntry. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput first-match regex could pick per-suite counts.\n- LOW (unfixed): writeMergeTelemetry duplicates NDJSON write logic from telemetry-writer.ts.\n- No integration test for full merge-then-validate flow with real git repo.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 16, Grep: 6, Glob: 5, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest run verbose (~50 lines), git diff (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One redundant glob search for workflow file\n\n###